BUG-10: Accepts Non-Numeric Text

Severity: Medium

Environment: Windows 11, Chrome Browser

Steps to Reproduce (STR):

1)Navigate to the "Expense Splitter."

2)In any numeric field, enter a single hyphen (-).

3)Click "Calculate."

Expected Result: An error message like "Please enter a valid number" should be displayed.

Actual Result: The app fails silently by treating the input as 0 or produces an Infinity error.

Evidence: 
 ![Screenshot showing accept non-numeric text](evidence\bug-10-non-numeric.png)